1
00:00:19,397 --> 00:00:20,855
(Wooju / Barcode Tinnasit)

2
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:25,188
(Raon / Jeff Satur)

3
00:00:27,313 --> 00:00:28,938
(Woo-hyuk / DION)

4
00:00:31,147 --> 00:00:33,063
(Q / Q)

5
00:00:35,313 --> 00:00:37,147
(Hachi / Jason) (Air / Alpha)

6
00:00:42,022 --> 00:00:46,772
"Wooju Bakery"
(Episode 1)

7
00:00:48,563 --> 00:00:50,063
"Here we go."

8
00:00:54,730 --> 00:00:59,355
(Wooju Bakery)

9
00:01:01,272 --> 00:01:01,938
Nice work.

10
00:01:02,063 --> 00:01:03,605
Hello, everyone.

11
00:01:04,063 --> 00:01:05,438
We're opening tomorrow.

12
00:01:05,563 --> 00:01:06,397
We hope you'll come visit.

13
00:01:06,522 --> 00:01:07,730
Wooju Bread.

14
00:01:08,647 --> 00:01:09,897
Wooju Bread.

15
00:01:10,022 --> 00:01:11,123
We're counting on your support.

16
00:01:11,147 --> 00:01:12,272
Wooju.

17
00:01:12,397 --> 00:01:13,647
Hyung.

18
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:26,105
Wooju, you're amazing.

19
00:01:26,230 --> 00:01:28,022
This bread looks beautiful!

20
00:01:28,772 --> 00:01:30,188
Here, try some.

21
00:01:30,313 --> 00:01:32,855
It's just a test batch.

22
00:01:37,980 --> 00:01:41,730
This... tastes a little...

23
00:01:43,647 --> 00:01:45,438
Did I add too much salt?

24
00:01:45,563 --> 00:01:46,563
Or is it the yeast?

25
00:01:46,605 --> 00:01:48,438
How can I open a bakery like this?

26
00:01:48,563 --> 00:01:51,480
Wooju, has your sense of
taste not come back yet?

27
00:01:53,730 --> 00:01:54,897
Don't worry.

28
00:01:55,022 --> 00:01:57,730
We still have Dad's recipes, right?

29
00:01:57,855 --> 00:01:59,772
Just follow the recipe book.

30
00:02:00,438 --> 00:02:02,230
Can I really do this?

31
00:02:02,355 --> 00:02:05,147
Of course you can. Let's
get ready for the opening.

32
00:02:08,105 --> 00:02:09,188
Are you hungry?

33
00:02:09,313 --> 00:02:10,438
Me?

34
00:02:11,188 --> 00:02:12,480
I'll just eat the bread.

35
00:02:16,897 --> 00:02:18,855
Didn't you just say it tastes weird?

36
00:02:19,980 --> 00:02:21,647
But you made it. I'm heading out.

37
00:02:21,772 --> 00:02:23,855
See you later, hyung.

38
00:02:42,813 --> 00:02:48,313
Is this where they sell the most delicious
and beautiful bread in the universe?

39
00:02:50,563 --> 00:02:51,272
Welcome.

40
00:02:51,397 --> 00:02:53,730
This is "Wooju Bakery."

41
00:02:53,855 --> 00:02:55,105
I'm sorry, but...

42
00:02:55,230 --> 00:02:56,438
All the bread in our shop...

43
00:02:56,563 --> 00:02:58,605
is already sold out for today.

44
00:03:00,522 --> 00:03:02,063
I came all this way just to try it.

45
00:03:02,188 --> 00:03:04,897
It's such a shame I can't have any.

46
00:03:06,438 --> 00:03:07,438
(Closed)

47
00:03:08,772 --> 00:03:09,772
(Open)

48
00:03:37,813 --> 00:03:40,522
Dad, where do stars come from?

49
00:03:40,848 --> 00:03:44,348
Stars come from a
faraway "universe" [wooju].

50
00:03:46,004 --> 00:03:48,605
Wooju, isn't that my name?

51
00:03:48,730 --> 00:03:50,105
That's right.

52
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:54,355
And the universe is
full of delicious bread.

53
00:03:55,188 --> 00:03:57,480
Wow, it looks so delicious!

54
00:04:02,147 --> 00:04:03,313
Huh?

55
00:04:04,272 --> 00:04:06,647
Dad, where did you go?

56
00:04:06,772 --> 00:04:09,647
Wooju, it's okay. Don't worry.

57
00:04:11,105 --> 00:04:14,563
Dad will always be by your side.

58
00:04:15,105 --> 00:04:16,438
Dad?

59
00:04:18,397 --> 00:04:21,522
Dad!

60
00:04:23,563 --> 00:04:24,772
Don't be afraid.

61
00:04:24,897 --> 00:04:27,605
When stars are first
born, they always tremble.

62
00:04:27,730 --> 00:04:29,772
My Wooju, let's meet again!

63
00:04:29,897 --> 00:04:31,313
Dad, where are you going?

64
00:04:32,688 --> 00:04:36,938
Dad, take me with you! I'm scared!

65
00:04:37,855 --> 00:04:39,355
Dad!

66
00:05:10,188 --> 00:05:11,647
My home!

67
00:05:21,147 --> 00:05:22,397
You guys!

68
00:05:23,188 --> 00:05:24,522
Look!

69
00:05:25,147 --> 00:05:25,980
Earthling!

70
00:05:26,105 --> 00:05:27,355
Don't be alarmed.

71
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:30,022
This is just a regular landing accident.

72
00:05:30,147 --> 00:05:31,772
Who are you people?

73
00:05:35,022 --> 00:05:37,063
Can you understand me, Earthling?

74
00:05:41,438 --> 00:05:44,188
Hachi! Is the translator broken?

75
00:05:44,313 --> 00:05:45,813
No, it is working well.

76
00:05:45,938 --> 00:05:47,980
Then why are you speaking
a different language?

77
00:05:48,105 --> 00:05:49,730
I like this language.

78
00:05:49,855 --> 00:05:51,355
I can speak Thai and English.

79
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,980
Stop messing around.

80
00:05:53,105 --> 00:05:54,897
Who on earth are you?

81
00:05:58,730 --> 00:06:04,813
My name is Blablalis
Romoromorian Ardi Raon.

82
00:06:04,938 --> 00:06:10,605
We're from the planet Kauncilion.

83
00:06:11,563 --> 00:06:13,272
I don't care who you are.

84
00:06:13,397 --> 00:06:16,813
You're the ones who wrecked
my bakery, aren't you?

85
00:06:17,772 --> 00:06:19,480
How are you going to pay for my bakery?

86
00:06:19,605 --> 00:06:23,355
Earthling, your body's
chemical levels are surging!

87
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:25,480
You should lower your blood pressure.

88
00:06:25,605 --> 00:06:27,081
Hachi, how do you say
that in the local language?

89
00:06:27,106 --> 00:06:27,814
Take it easy!

90
00:06:27,938 --> 00:06:28,772
Hey!

91
00:06:28,897 --> 00:06:30,355
How can I be calm?

92
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:33,331
The grand opening is tomorrow, and
you crash into my shop and set it on fire!

93
00:06:33,355 --> 00:06:34,605
What do you want me to do?

94
00:06:34,730 --> 00:06:37,313
It was just a regular landing accident.

95
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:38,730
Anyway, don't worry.

96
00:06:38,855 --> 00:06:41,272
It'll be covered by our
space travel insurance.

97
00:06:41,397 --> 00:06:42,647
Insurance money?

98
00:06:47,188 --> 00:06:48,313
When will I get it?

99
00:06:50,438 --> 00:06:52,522
For them to investigate this far...

100
00:06:52,647 --> 00:06:55,897
In Earth time, it would be about...

101
00:06:58,563 --> 00:06:59,688
A year?

102
00:07:00,397 --> 00:07:03,438
A year? Are you kidding me?

103
00:07:03,563 --> 00:07:05,313
I have a bakery to open tomorrow!

104
00:07:05,438 --> 00:07:06,688
Let's go to the police station.

105
00:07:06,813 --> 00:07:08,063
The police?

106
00:07:10,522 --> 00:07:12,980
The kind that lock us up and dissect us?

107
00:07:13,313 --> 00:07:15,272
Is that an Earthling custom?

108
00:07:16,105 --> 00:07:18,313
- Hey!
- Let's make a deal.

109
00:07:19,063 --> 00:07:19,813
What kind of deal?

110
00:07:19,938 --> 00:07:21,230
We have money in our spaceship.

111
00:07:21,355 --> 00:07:23,105
I'll go exchange it quickly.

112
00:07:23,230 --> 00:07:24,498
I'll give it to you before the
insurance money comes through.

113
00:07:24,522 --> 00:07:26,022
What kind of nonsense is this?

114
00:07:26,147 --> 00:07:27,563
That piece of junk is a spaceship?

115
00:07:27,688 --> 00:07:28,980
Yes, a spaceship.

116
00:07:29,105 --> 00:07:30,147
That's a car.

117
00:07:30,272 --> 00:07:33,147
Where the hell did you learn Thai?

118
00:07:33,605 --> 00:07:36,563
Hachi! This Earthling's
adrenaline is through the roof.

119
00:07:36,688 --> 00:07:38,488
He might get too excited
and start screaming.

120
00:07:38,563 --> 00:07:39,980
Stabilize his nerve cells, quickly.

121
00:07:40,105 --> 00:07:41,938
You maniacs!

122
00:07:47,772 --> 00:07:48,772
Prince.

123
00:07:48,813 --> 00:07:49,938
Hachi.

124
00:07:50,647 --> 00:07:52,063
Why did you shoot him?

125
00:07:52,188 --> 00:07:53,813
I didn't kill him.

126
00:07:59,105 --> 00:08:00,647
Let's get out of here first.

127
00:08:11,605 --> 00:08:14,813
So you're saying there were
strange men here just now?

128
00:08:14,938 --> 00:08:16,397
Are you sure you didn't see things?

129
00:08:16,522 --> 00:08:17,897
Dong-myeong is here.

130
00:08:18,688 --> 00:08:19,897
Dong-myeong...

131
00:08:20,230 --> 00:08:21,480
Wooju!

132
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:24,480
Are you hurt?

133
00:08:26,147 --> 00:08:27,397
Are you okay?

134
00:08:27,522 --> 00:08:29,772
You're not even in night shift today, though.

135
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:31,772
Yes, sir.

136
00:08:32,897 --> 00:08:35,313
But you know the owner of this bakery?

137
00:08:35,438 --> 00:08:38,730
We've practically lived
together since we were kids.

138
00:08:38,855 --> 00:08:41,022
He's like a real brother to me.

139
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:43,438
Wooju, are you all right?

140
00:08:43,563 --> 00:08:44,772
It's the rescue team, right?

141
00:08:46,897 --> 00:08:48,355
I think it's the rescue team?

142
00:08:50,522 --> 00:08:53,480
What kind of rescue team is this sloppy?

143
00:08:54,605 --> 00:08:55,980
It looks like a crash landing.

144
00:08:56,105 --> 00:08:59,022
Bro, what should I do?

145
00:08:59,147 --> 00:09:00,707
The shop was supposed to open tomorrow.

146
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:02,605
It's all ruined.

147
00:09:02,730 --> 00:09:03,980
It's going to be okay.

148
00:09:04,397 --> 00:09:07,938
There's a lot of smoke, but
not much actually burned.

149
00:09:09,522 --> 00:09:11,188
Though the walls are a bit cracked.

150
00:09:11,855 --> 00:09:14,335
Let's clean this up first, and
we'll open tomorrow as planned.

151
00:09:14,855 --> 00:09:17,897
Hyung, we have to find them.

152
00:09:18,855 --> 00:09:20,605
I've never seen those two Thai guys before.

153
00:09:20,730 --> 00:09:22,063
But I'm sure of it.

154
00:09:23,188 --> 00:09:24,855
They're definitely the culprits.

155
00:09:26,938 --> 00:09:28,188
Thai guys?

156
00:09:30,105 --> 00:09:32,355
Got it. Wooju, wait here for a second.

157
00:09:35,813 --> 00:09:38,230
The rescue team's investigation
came to the same conclusion.

158
00:09:38,355 --> 00:09:41,188
It was just a lot of smoke, not a big fire.

159
00:09:41,313 --> 00:09:46,105
The owner here said a car crashed
into the shop and started a huge fire.

160
00:09:46,305 --> 00:09:49,304
As you can see, there are
almost no signs of a fire.

161
00:09:49,305 --> 00:09:52,604
He was probably drunk
driving. That's got to be it.

162
00:09:52,605 --> 00:09:54,522
It looks like he just
crashed straight into it.

163
00:09:54,647 --> 00:09:58,438
He said that when the fire started,
there were two Thai-speaking men here.

164
00:09:58,563 --> 00:10:02,105
There are no signs of a break-in at all.

165
00:10:03,605 --> 00:10:05,063
We have our conclusion.

166
00:10:13,063 --> 00:10:15,730
The car crashed, creating sparks.

167
00:10:15,855 --> 00:10:20,313
Then it hit the gas tank, "Bang!"

168
00:10:20,438 --> 00:10:23,563
That matches the explosion
the residents heard.

169
00:10:24,230 --> 00:10:26,605
But there are no signs of a gas explosion.

170
00:10:26,730 --> 00:10:29,105
Just write what I told you to write.

171
00:10:29,230 --> 00:10:32,647
No one's going to check anyway.

172
00:10:51,438 --> 00:10:53,188
You guys, don't run!

173
00:10:53,522 --> 00:10:55,230
Hey, stop!

174
00:10:55,355 --> 00:10:56,897
Stop right there!

175
00:10:57,022 --> 00:10:58,230
Don't run.

176
00:10:58,605 --> 00:11:00,022
Hyung! Hyung!

177
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:01,813
Wooju!

178
00:11:02,897 --> 00:11:04,438
I really saw them.

179
00:11:06,272 --> 00:11:10,647
I saw them clearly.

180
00:11:10,772 --> 00:11:13,105
I saw both of their faces.

181
00:11:13,230 --> 00:11:14,897
What did they look like?

182
00:11:15,022 --> 00:11:19,272
One was wearing a sparkly stage outfit.

183
00:11:19,647 --> 00:11:22,980
The other was in a dog onesie.

184
00:11:23,105 --> 00:11:24,522
They were both weird.

185
00:11:29,688 --> 00:11:32,355
Hyung, tonight...

186
00:11:32,980 --> 00:11:37,313
Can I sleep at your
place? I'm a little scared.

187
00:11:41,897 --> 00:11:44,522
I'm really scared. Please let me stay.

188
00:11:44,647 --> 00:11:47,047
It's not like we didn't have
sleepovers when we were kids...

189
00:12:18,730 --> 00:12:21,563
Who are you, and what are you doing here?

190
00:12:23,355 --> 00:12:25,147
Just as I thought.

191
00:12:25,272 --> 00:12:28,313
Humans have such bad memories.

192
00:12:28,647 --> 00:12:30,980
I'll say it again.

193
00:12:31,105 --> 00:12:38,063
My name is Blablalis
Romoromorian Ardi Raon.

194
00:12:38,188 --> 00:12:41,355
You can just call me Raon. This is Hachi.

195
00:12:49,147 --> 00:12:50,230
Are you guys real?

196
00:12:50,355 --> 00:12:51,563
I'm not seeing things, am I?

197
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:54,365
From a quantum mechanics perspective,
particles also have the properties of waves.

198
00:12:54,397 --> 00:12:56,039
And waves have the properties of particles.

199
00:12:56,063 --> 00:12:58,897
So determining if something truly exists
is not that simple.

200
00:12:59,022 --> 00:13:00,855
"I think, therefore I am."

201
00:13:00,980 --> 00:13:02,272
Then what are you?

202
00:13:02,397 --> 00:13:03,897
Walking around in a dog costume?

203
00:13:04,855 --> 00:13:06,605
What Hachi is wearing is special equipment.

204
00:13:06,730 --> 00:13:10,313
It's the uniform of the kingdom's
top astronaut and engineer.

205
00:13:11,022 --> 00:13:13,414
It can also transform into a humanoid form
during long voyages to save energy.

206
00:13:13,438 --> 00:13:15,605
I have no idea what you're talking about.

207
00:13:15,730 --> 00:13:18,980
Who are you, and why are you here?

208
00:13:22,772 --> 00:13:25,022
From the perspective of Earthlings...

209
00:13:26,230 --> 00:13:27,897
we're aliens.

210
00:13:28,022 --> 00:13:30,272
What? Aliens?

211
00:13:40,563 --> 00:13:41,897
What do you think you're doing?

212
00:13:53,022 --> 00:13:53,772
You lunatics.

213
00:13:53,897 --> 00:13:56,097
You set fire to my place
and think you can just run off?

214
00:13:56,147 --> 00:13:56,813
What on earth is going on?

215
00:13:56,931 --> 00:13:57,806
Barging into my room...

216
00:13:57,938 --> 00:14:00,188
Are you trying to end up in jail?

217
00:14:01,022 --> 00:14:02,480
Jail food?

218
00:14:02,813 --> 00:14:06,855
You mean that stuff that
was just made downstairs?

219
00:14:06,980 --> 00:14:09,480
That stuff was disgusting.

220
00:14:10,063 --> 00:14:12,355
If we get locked up and have to eat that...

221
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:13,522
it would be miserable.

222
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:14,681
It was terrible.

223
00:14:14,813 --> 00:14:18,147
What... are you people talking about?

224
00:14:27,147 --> 00:14:28,730
Who's this guy?

225
00:14:32,729 --> 00:14:33,938
(Wooju Bakery)

226
00:14:34,688 --> 00:14:36,105
There's one over there.

227
00:14:37,855 --> 00:14:38,855
And another one there.

228
00:14:41,688 --> 00:14:43,063
This is unacceptable!

229
00:15:21,355 --> 00:15:23,147
Clean this mess up, you freak!

230
00:15:23,272 --> 00:15:24,938
Looks like you're the freak here.

231
00:15:34,688 --> 00:15:37,897
We... didn't order jjajangmyeon, though.

232
00:15:39,230 --> 00:15:39,897
Is that the rescue team?

233
00:15:40,022 --> 00:15:40,813
Who are you?

234
00:15:40,938 --> 00:15:45,230
I'm Jirol. I transport
the galaxy's food supply.

235
00:15:45,855 --> 00:15:48,147
The galaxy's food supply?

236
00:15:53,272 --> 00:15:54,938
So it really was a crash landing.

237
00:15:55,063 --> 00:15:57,897
I thought it was the rescue team.
I got my hopes up for nothing.

238
00:15:58,022 --> 00:16:01,563
You'll have to bite the
bullet and stick it out here too.

239
00:16:02,105 --> 00:16:03,480
But we'll be going back soon.

240
00:16:03,605 --> 00:16:05,498
That's what I thought,
that I'd be back home soon.

241
00:16:05,522 --> 00:16:07,272
But in Earth time...

242
00:16:07,397 --> 00:16:09,313
it's been a hundred years. A full century.

243
00:16:09,438 --> 00:16:12,438
We're from the House of Blablalis.

244
00:16:15,355 --> 00:16:18,313
What? A prince of Blablalis?

245
00:16:18,438 --> 00:16:22,022
The prince from the Kauncilion?

246
00:16:26,230 --> 00:16:30,897
Old man!

247
00:16:31,522 --> 00:16:33,688
See? I told you I was right.

248
00:16:35,313 --> 00:16:37,272
That guy! He's actual royalty.

249
00:16:37,397 --> 00:16:39,230
Blablalis?

250
00:16:39,280 --> 00:16:40,706
Doesn't that make him the Crown Prince?

251
00:16:40,730 --> 00:16:41,873
It looks like they really did crash-land.

252
00:16:41,897 --> 00:16:44,730
If he's the Crown Prince, a
rescue team is sure to come.

253
00:16:44,855 --> 00:16:46,688
Get closer. Stick with them.

254
00:16:46,813 --> 00:16:49,813
If we want to get out of here with
them, we need to get on their good side.

255
00:16:49,980 --> 00:16:52,480
The House of Blablaris...

256
00:16:52,605 --> 00:16:56,313
is the supreme royal family that unites
hundreds of thousands of alien species.

257
00:16:56,438 --> 00:17:00,230
Without them, the galaxy
would be in total chaos.

258
00:17:00,355 --> 00:17:04,230
A rescue team will definitely come for
the Prince of Blablaris.

259
00:17:04,355 --> 00:17:05,063
And that means...

260
00:17:05,188 --> 00:17:09,355
after 116 years, 8 months,
and 37 days on Earth...

261
00:17:09,480 --> 00:17:11,105
I can finally go home.

262
00:17:11,230 --> 00:17:13,039
Are you wondering why
an alien looks so... normal?

263
00:17:13,063 --> 00:17:16,105
What, you thought we'd
look like this? Or maybe this?

264
00:17:16,230 --> 00:17:18,563
You Earthlings have
such a poor imagination.

265
00:17:18,688 --> 00:17:20,563
Is it all the oxygen you breathe?

266
00:17:20,688 --> 00:17:23,022
Aliens don't have a fixed appearance.

267
00:17:23,147 --> 00:17:26,605
We just take this form
to blend in with you.

268
00:17:26,730 --> 00:17:28,730
So while we wait to be rescued...

269
00:17:28,855 --> 00:17:30,688
some of us open auto repair shops,

270
00:17:30,813 --> 00:17:32,230
some become fortune-tellers,

271
00:17:32,355 --> 00:17:34,272
and others get into pyramid schemes.

272
00:17:34,397 --> 00:17:37,317
Me? As you can see, I just play the
fool and hang around the neighborhood.

273
00:17:37,438 --> 00:17:38,623
What, you still don't believe me?

274
00:17:38,647 --> 00:17:40,480
You want proof?

275
00:17:40,605 --> 00:17:42,605
Then put on some music with a beat.

276
00:17:43,105 --> 00:17:45,897
Ah... I can't stop!

277
00:17:46,147 --> 00:17:48,313
If they dance, they must be an alien.

278
00:17:48,438 --> 00:17:50,980
We can't help but move when we hear a beat.

279
00:17:52,313 --> 00:17:54,272
Okay, shh! Don't get too friendly.

280
00:17:54,397 --> 00:17:57,022
We've been living among you all along.

281
00:17:57,605 --> 00:17:59,980
Mwahahahaha!

282
00:18:00,897 --> 00:18:02,188
About what happened yesterday...

283
00:18:02,313 --> 00:18:05,688
The victim said they saw a stranger.

284
00:18:05,813 --> 00:18:07,022
Sir.

285
00:18:09,313 --> 00:18:12,730
This is a metal fragment we
found at the scene yesterday.

286
00:18:12,855 --> 00:18:15,522
It's not any metal found on Earth.

287
00:18:18,813 --> 00:18:21,355
Hello, is this the psychiatric hospital?

288
00:18:22,272 --> 00:18:24,373
I'd like to bring someone
in for an appointment at two.

289
00:18:24,397 --> 00:18:25,480
Okay.

290
00:18:26,188 --> 00:18:27,855
He said to come by at two.

291
00:18:28,772 --> 00:18:30,730
Take this with you.

292
00:18:32,015 --> 00:18:34,181
I don't need a shrink,
this needs to be sent to NASA.

293
00:18:35,772 --> 00:18:37,147
Just get back to work.

294
00:18:38,730 --> 00:18:40,250
What are we going to do with this car?

295
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:44,022
That's not a car. It's a spaceship.

296
00:18:44,522 --> 00:18:47,813
It just took a form that
would be familiar to Earthlings.

297
00:18:47,938 --> 00:18:50,605
Cut the crap. What are
we doing with this thing?

298
00:18:55,063 --> 00:18:56,980
Let's just leave it here for now.

299
00:18:57,105 --> 00:19:00,480
It'll be a nice tourist
attraction for the Earthlings.

300
00:19:07,772 --> 00:19:09,855
Why do we have to put everything back?

301
00:19:09,980 --> 00:19:11,730
Is that a rule on Earth?

302
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:15,873
The grand opening is
delayed because of you.

303
00:19:15,897 --> 00:19:18,355
Didn't you say you'd pay me back in cash?

304
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:20,105
Then give me the money now!

305
00:19:20,230 --> 00:19:22,105
Right now...

306
00:19:24,605 --> 00:19:26,355
I don't have any...

307
00:19:27,438 --> 00:19:27,938
money.

308
00:19:28,063 --> 00:19:30,383
"Currency Exchange - Earth
Branch 16 / House of Blablaris"

309
00:19:32,813 --> 00:19:34,188
What's that?

310
00:19:34,688 --> 00:19:36,813
Isn't that just a kid's marble?

311
00:19:37,897 --> 00:19:39,897
This is money where I come from.

312
00:19:41,355 --> 00:19:42,897
And it's very valuable.

313
00:19:43,397 --> 00:19:45,230
It's just been shrunken down to this size.

314
00:19:46,355 --> 00:19:48,022
It just looks like a marble to me.

315
00:19:50,188 --> 00:19:51,022
Hold on.

316
00:19:51,147 --> 00:19:54,938
(Incantation)

317
00:19:55,063 --> 00:19:56,272
What is that?

318
00:19:56,397 --> 00:19:57,772
See?

319
00:20:07,063 --> 00:20:10,480
(Incantation)

320
00:20:25,605 --> 00:20:26,772
What is that?

321
00:20:27,813 --> 00:20:29,522
Is that an Earthling?

322
00:20:29,647 --> 00:20:32,563
Why did you bring an
Earthling to an exchange?

323
00:20:32,688 --> 00:20:33,938
That's against the rules.

324
00:20:34,063 --> 00:20:37,563
We just crash-landed yesterday.
We don't know the rules.

325
00:20:37,688 --> 00:20:38,897
Sorry.

326
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:41,230
The signal is weak here on Earth.

327
00:20:41,355 --> 00:20:43,688
So foreign currency is almost worthless.

328
00:20:43,813 --> 00:20:45,373
Do you still want to make the exchange?

329
00:20:48,647 --> 00:20:49,772
Be honest with me.

330
00:20:49,897 --> 00:20:51,355
You're a con artist, aren't you?

331
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:53,720
This isn't even enough to
cover the repairs for my shop.

332
00:20:54,230 --> 00:20:56,730
Let alone be enough for compensation.

333
00:20:57,438 --> 00:20:58,688
Oh, really?

334
00:20:59,813 --> 00:21:00,855
So...

335
00:21:00,980 --> 00:21:02,688
what can you do with this much money?

336
00:21:02,813 --> 00:21:05,230
Maybe where you're from,

337
00:21:05,355 --> 00:21:06,813
this is a month's salary.

338
00:21:06,938 --> 00:21:10,397
But here, you can earn this
by working hard for 15 hours.

339
00:21:10,522 --> 00:21:11,855
What?

340
00:21:11,980 --> 00:21:13,230
Fifteen hours?

341
00:21:22,772 --> 00:21:24,355
Hold your hands up.

342
00:21:25,313 --> 00:21:27,522
This is...
What are you doing?

343
00:21:27,647 --> 00:21:28,647
I'm putting you to work.

344
00:21:28,730 --> 00:21:30,563
So I don't have to pay you?

345
00:21:30,688 --> 00:21:31,563
What are you talking about?

346
00:21:31,688 --> 00:21:34,063
Of course you have to pay me back.

347
00:21:35,147 --> 00:21:36,730
Then I don't want to work.

348
00:21:37,688 --> 00:21:39,605
I'd rather just pay you the money.

349
00:21:41,522 --> 00:21:42,938
This is unbelievable.

350
00:21:43,063 --> 00:21:45,063
You're not even a
little bit sorry, are you?

351
00:21:45,188 --> 00:21:47,355
Don't you see all this burnt equipment?

352
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:49,272
And the power outage?

353
00:21:49,397 --> 00:21:51,957
I'm trying to cut you some slack
since you're stranded on Earth.

354
00:21:52,022 --> 00:21:53,980
I'm not holding it against you.

355
00:21:56,272 --> 00:21:57,688
Sign your name here.

356
00:21:57,813 --> 00:21:58,605
What's this?

357
00:21:58,730 --> 00:21:59,813
It's a contract.

358
00:21:59,938 --> 00:22:03,063
You'll work for me for 10
years until you pay off your debt.

359
00:22:03,188 --> 00:22:05,230
That includes repair costs and interest.

360
00:22:12,563 --> 00:22:15,355
Oh shit! Prince, the police are here.

361
00:22:16,230 --> 00:22:18,272
You called the police?

362
00:22:20,355 --> 00:22:22,155
I'll work at your bakery
to pay off the debt.

363
00:22:27,938 --> 00:22:29,081
Please, don't call the police.

364
00:22:29,105 --> 00:22:30,813
(Wooju Bakery)

365
00:22:37,105 --> 00:22:39,188
We just arrived on earth with the princess.

366
00:22:40,390 --> 00:22:45,348
We plan to rescue the prince by searching
the place where the prince is presumed to be.

367
00:22:54,605 --> 00:22:56,897
The princess has a question.

368
00:22:57,813 --> 00:22:59,563
If we've found the prince,

369
00:23:00,313 --> 00:23:01,938
will the King keep his promise?
